Common Security Issues seen in the cloud

1. Open (i.e. Public) S3 buckets
2. S3 buckets/ EBS Volumes/ data disks not encrypted at rest
3. Network ACL's and Security groups allow public access (both ingress and egress)
4. Container registries are publicly acessible
5. Key vaults are not monitored/ logged
6. VPC's don't have flow logs enabled
7. Creation/ updation/ deletion of ACL's is not monitored
8. Inconsistent/ Missing Tagging
9. No Exception Tagging
10. Leading practise alerts for suspicious AWS events not monitored
